   "source": [
    "## Area Below Function\n",
    "\n",
    "Plots out a function and highlights graphically the area below the function from a lower and to an upper limit -- the integral value of the function between the lower and upper limits. The integral (value) to be illustrated is $\\begin{align}\\int_{a}^{b} f(x) \\,dx\\end{align}$ with $\\begin{align}f(x) = \\frac{1}{2} * e^x + 1\\end{align}$, $\\begin{align}a = \\frac{1}{2}\\end{align}$, and $\\begin{align}b = \\frac{3}{2}\\end{align}$\n",
    "\n",
    "<br>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "48ad4124-e357-4a8f-9ce9-0309dc979289",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# define the function we're measuring\n",
    "def func(x):\n",
    "    return 0.5 * np.exp(x) + 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "185eaa91-ed43-4f1f-ab0c-c1e27dda9915",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# set the variables\n",
    "a, b = 0.5, 1.5\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0, 2)\n",
    "y = func(x)\n",
    "Ix = np.linspace(a, b)\n",
    "Iy = func(Ix)\n",
    "verts = [(a, 0)] + list(zip(Ix, Iy)) + [(b, 0)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "6f2ffe91-da08-44a6-b732-d6c3ff684cb7",
